msDesc.head: Richard of St Victor, Commentary on Revelation

supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation in pencil. De templo aperto

collation.catchwords: Catchwords at the end of every quire.

p.note: Top left corner, in red ink by a modern hand: A 166 a; bottom right corner in blue ink: 1944/18 (accession number); next to it: H. 4..

binding.p: Modern or early modern binding. Limp binding in green leather. , red leather label with text in gold: COMMENT IN APOCALIP; green leather label with text in gold: MS DU XIV SIECLE; National Library book label with current signum.
binding.condition: Leather worn, spine partially torn off at the top.

history.provenance: Origin and provenance unknown. On a modern addition orginally contained information about a previous owner, but the name has been erased. One of the labels on is in French, which indicates a provenance in France or a French speaking environment.
history.acquisition: Purchased by the National Library from the baroness Elise Åkerhielm of Anneberg, Gustavsberg, .

msItem.title: Commentary on Revelation
msItem.rubric: Incipit prologus in exposicione libri apocalipsis
msItem.incipit: Accipe karissime frater hoc sentenciarum munus
msItem.explicit: qui nec loco capitur nec tempore mutatur immensus et eternus qui est deus benedictus in secula seculorum amen
msItem.note: Each book is introduced by a list of chapters.

supportDesc.condition: Parchment worn and stained; holes in the parchment in several places, no loss of text.

handDesc.handNote: Late pregothic or early Gothic textualis.

p.note: Bottom of the page, in brown ink by a modern hand: Ex Bibliotheca (the rest erased); National Library stamp.
Bottom of page in black ink by a medieval hand: capitula n in inuerso lxxxix.
Drawings of a sword and a person in profile in the margins.

Frequent marginal addtions by several medieval hands. Many are corrections or additions of missing passages keyed to the text with signe-de-renvoi, others seem to be comments on the text. Frequent manicules in different styles, nota-marks, and other symbols in the margin. On there are extensive additions in brown ink in the margin.

decoDesc.p: Main text in black ink, rubrics in red, capitals touched in red, lemmata underlined in red.
decoDesc.decoNote: : Opening plain initial A over 4 lines in red with interior reserved shapes. : paragraphs are opened by plain initials over 2 lines in red.
